node.text: @c.g.nelson love you!
👍🏾Perfectly stated! 🥂 Cheers on a great career and good luck to you on your next chapter!

For the last 13 years, this news lady has always heard, “You have such a cool job.”
And what a ride it’s been. —————————-
I’ve interviewed two Presidents, famous actors, and musicians on red carpets. 
I’ve stared into the eyes of a woman who killed her adopted daughter and felt pure evil for the first time. 
I stood near the finish line of the Boston Marathon and witnessed the life changing aftermath of immense tragedy. 
I’ve frozen in blizzards, been battered reporting during severe storms, and anchored live during not one - but two - tornadoes.
I’ve met some of my dearest friends and incredible women in newsrooms across the country (including @azgirlinil, @linzkatz24, @adrianneklabik, @knelsonau2006 and @kerrykavanaugh)
I’ve had the honor of spending time with American heroes, and sometimes sharing their stories when they didn’t make it home. ————————
But it would be disingenuous if I failed to address the challenges of this business that have discouraged so many. 
The stolen weekends, the holidays missed, and the constant disappointment of letting down your loved ones when the job came first. 
The self loathing of knocking on the door of a family who just lost a child, a spouse or a friend, and feeling like you’re only extorting their grief. 
The disgust at having to urinate in a bush somewhere because you couldn’t leave a scene and there were no bathrooms for miles. 
Sexual harassment from online trolls, newsmakers and male colleagues, including my own #MeToo moment with someone I thought was a trusted mentor.
The thousands of dollars in credit card debt from a job that didn’t pay nearly enough...no matter what level you reached. ———————-
Yet, it was still more sweet than bitter. And at the end of it all, I am left humbled by the people who, every single day, shared their darkest moments, their biggest victories, and their homes with me - a stranger - without asking anything in return. 
As I prepare to trade in my microphone for the next “cool job,” I’m grateful for lucky number 13.
👏👏👏 This was so perfectly said. All of it. You’re such an amazing journalist! I can’t wait to see what you do next!!!!
You are a rock solid journalist and such a lovely person. I know you will succeed no matter what you do next. Im thankful we got to work together. I wish you all the best. Xoxo 😘
So excited for you lady! Can’t wait to see what’s next 😘
I seriously can’t believe you’re out. We need a phone date.
I have no doubt that you'll crush whatever is next!! (What _is_ next?)
So good! I’m so happy for you. You’re going to continue to be amazing where ever you go!! Can’t wait to see the great things in store!
Good luck!
Best wishes for whatever your future brings! ❤️
Congratulations on your next chapter!  You will be missed!

Congratulations on your next challenge!! Journalism is the best job in the world and the worst job too. You see people at their best and their worst moments. But you’ve always done it with a smile. It’s been a joy to work beside you at times. Best of luck!
@kathrynburcham beautifully said! You were absolutely one of the best. You’re going to love your next chapter ❤️
Congrats on your next chapter! You are an inspiration.
Congrats to you for making the leap! Happy for you and can’t wait to see what’s next ❤️
@juliannemcc nope. Headed to chicago where the people are almost as nice as southerners 😉
Are you coming back to Charlotte??💕
Well said. Fair winds and following seas

First @jesssicamreyes and now you? What the heck is going on over there?!? I’m sorry to see you go but happy that you are on to something better for you. I’ve always believed if you don’t live what you’re doing, you need to do be doing something else.
For what it’s worth, I wish you all the best.
Best of Luck ... we will miss seeing u @ Trilogy Salon💕
Love 4ever frand! I’m so excited to be within driving distance again!!!! Welcome to life on the other side 😘
Congratulations on a wonderful journalism career! Best of luck in your next adventure!
So well said! You’re so talented and any employer is beyond lucky to have you. Sending you love and luck in your next chapter ❤️
‪Thank for for the honest post. Few people talk about the difficulties and sacrifices of the business. All the best. ‬
@c.g.nelson love you!
Good Luck on your next “cool job”. Can’t wait to see you when you come to the “Inlet”. So glad Kristin became part of your life because that brought you into ours. 😍
👍🏾Perfectly stated! 🥂 Cheers on a great career and good luck to you on your next chapter!
